{
  "target": "simulation",
  "kind": "simulation",
  "source_test": "HEC.FDA.Model/compute/ImpactAreaScenarioSimulation.cs PopulateRandomNumbers (202-252), GetFrequencyStageSample (405-433), GetStageFreq (435-451) -- no dedicated upstream unit test exercises these private methods directly (both are private in C#), so both cases are oracle-gate-reproduced directly against the real PopulateRandomNumbers + GetFrequencyStageSample via the emitter's public-access relaxation (same rationale as simulation_validation.json's can_compute/consequence_result_count cases).",
  "note": "Reuses simulation_validation.json's construct shape (impact_area_id, flow_frequency, flow_stage, stage_damage, optional non_failure_stage_damage) with one addition: flow_stage carries a damage_category so its CurveMetaData.IsNull is false -- required for PopulateRandomNumbers to actually call GenerateRandomNumbers on it (the C# gate is `!_DischargeStage.CurveMetaData.IsNull`, matching this port's `discharge_stage_.has_value() && !discharge_stage_->metadata().is_null()`); without it, the seeded case would throw 'Random numbers have not been created for UPD sampling'. stage_damage is empty ([]) -- not exercised by this fixture's methods. Both cases have no reg/unreg curve, no direct frequency-stage curve, and no interior/exterior curve, so GetFrequencyStageSample takes the simplest path: analytical bootstrap_to_paired_data (flow_frequency: Uniform(0,100000,1000)) composed with the flow_stage rating curve (X={0,100000}, Y=Uniform(0,0,10)/Uniform(0,30,10)), and ChannelStage/FloodplainStage are identical (no interior/exterior). `method` dispatches: frequency_stage_channel_yvals / frequency_stage_floodplain_yvals, args [min_iterations, max_iterations, iteration_number, compute_is_deterministic (0/1)] -- builds the simulation, calls populate_random_numbers(ConvergenceCriteria(min_iterations, max_iterations)), then get_frequency_stage_sample(compute_is_deterministic, iteration_number), returning ChannelStage.Yvals or FloodplainStage.Yvals (173-value vector, one per required_exceedance_probabilities() grid point). deterministic_no_rng needs no random numbers at all (compute_is_deterministic=true bypasses every Sample()/SamplePairedData(iteration) call in favor of central-tendency values) -- populate_random_numbers is still called first, matching the real Compute() call order, but is a no-op for this case's result. seeded_via_populated_random_numbers exercises the per-curve seeded RNG: FREQUENCY_SEED=1234 for the analytical flow_frequency distribution (ContinuousDistribution.GenerateRandomSamplesofNumbers) and STAGE_FLOW_SEED=3456 for the flow_stage rating curve (UncertainPairedData.GenerateRandomNumbers), both drawn from PopulateRandomNumbers with max_iterations=1000 -> quantityOfRandomNumbers=Convert.ToInt32(1000*1.25)=1250, well past iteration_number=1. All Yvals PIN (gate-captured against the real C#, never hand-derived, even though the deterministic case is in principle hand-derivable from Uniform's linear InverseCDF -- the seeded case is not, and consistent discipline across both cases is preferred).",
